<!--
  Help and FAQ page.
  WCAG 3.2.6: Accessible from the same position on every page (header icon).
  WCAG 1.3.1: Semantic sections with headings for screen reader navigation.
  WCAG 2.1.1: All content navigable via Tab and heading shortcuts.
  Uses <details>/<summary> for Q&A — natively accessible, Enter/Space to toggle.
-->

<style>
  /* Override base.css p { max-width: 65ch } for the help page */
  .help-page p { max-width: none; }
</style>

<div class="help-page" style="max-width:900px; margin:0 auto;">

  <h1>Help and FAQ</h1>
  <p style="color:var(--fp-text-2); margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-8);">
    Everything you need to know about FluentPath. Use the sections below to find answers to common questions.
  </p>

  <!-- Re-access onboarding -->
  <section aria-labelledby="onboarding-heading" style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-8);">
    <h2 id="onboarding-heading">Getting Started</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-4);">
      If you want to review how FluentPath works, you can revisit the welcome guide at any time.
    </p>
    <a href="/onboarding/1" class="btn btn-secondary">
      View the welcome guide again
    </a>
  </section>

  <!-- How skills are calculated -->
  <section aria-labelledby="skills-heading" style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-8);">
    <h2 id="skills-heading">How Your Skill Percentages Are Calculated</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-4);">
      Your progress page shows four skill areas. Each one is calculated based on the exercises you have completed:
    </p>

    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:var(--fp-space-3);">

      <article class="card">
        <h3 style="font-size:var(--fp-text-base); margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-1);">
          <span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> Reading
        </h3>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:0;">
          Based on reading exercises — short stories at your level with optional audio support. You read the text and mark it as completed. Your percentage reflects how many reading exercises you have finished out of the total available.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3 style="font-size:var(--fp-text-base); margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-1);">
          <span aria-hidden="true">🎧</span> Listening
        </h3>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:0;">
          Based on two types of exercises: dictation (listen and type the full sentence) and listening comprehension (listen and choose the missing word). Both count toward your listening percentage.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3 style="font-size:var(--fp-text-base); margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-1);">
          <span aria-hidden="true">🗣</span> Speaking
        </h3>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:0;">
          Based on speaking practice exercises — you listen to a model sentence and repeat it out loud. The app does not evaluate your pronunciation, but completing the practice counts toward your speaking progress.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3 style="font-size:var(--fp-text-base); margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-1);">
          <span aria-hidden="true">✏️</span> Writing
        </h3>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:0;">
          Combines grammar and translation exercises. Grammar exercises (multiple choice) and translation exercises (type the sentence in English) both count toward your writing percentage. Word bank exercises also count here.
        </p>
      </article>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Lessons and content -->
  <section aria-labelledby="content-heading" style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-8);">
    <h2 id="content-heading">What You Will Find in Lessons</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-4);">
      Each lesson contains a mix of exercises and vocabulary cards:
    </p>

    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:var(--fp-space-3);">

      <article class="card">
        <h3 style="font-size:var(--fp-text-base); margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-1);">Exercises</h3>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:0;">
          Each lesson has multiple exercise types: reading stories, listening dictation, listening comprehension, speaking practice, translation, grammar (multiple choice), and word bank. You get feedback after every exercise with a tip explaining the correct answer.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3 style="font-size:var(--fp-text-base); margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-1);">Vocabulary Cards</h3>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:0;">
          Every lesson has a vocabulary section with key words, their definitions, and example sentences. These are always visible — no need to hover or click to reveal them. Review the vocabulary before starting the exercises for best results.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3 style="font-size:var(--fp-text-base); margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-1);">Hints and Pro-Tips</h3>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:0;">
          When you answer incorrectly, the feedback page shows a Pro-Tip explaining the grammar rule or vocabulary pattern you missed. Translation exercises also have word hints available that you can expand to see a list of suggested words.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3 style="font-size:var(--fp-text-base); margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-1);">Stories by Level</h3>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:0;">
          Reading exercises include short stories matched to your level. Beginner stories use simple present tense and basic vocabulary. Elementary stories introduce past tenses and more complex sentence structures. Each story has an optional audio version you can listen to while reading.
        </p>
      </article>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Level Assessment -->
  <section aria-labelledby="assessment-heading" style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-8);">
    <h2 id="assessment-heading">Level Assessment</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-4);">
      The level assessment is a short test that determines your starting point. You can take it from the dashboard or the sidebar. Before starting, you can choose whether to use a timer or not — there is no penalty for disabling the timer.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-4);">
      If you want to retake the assessment to update your level, you can do so here:
    </p>
    <a href="/assessment/retake" class="btn btn-secondary" style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-4);">
      Retake level assessment
    </a>
    <p>
      Based on your score, you will start one of three levels:
    </p>
    <ul style="margin:var(--fp-space-3) 0 var(--fp-space-4) var(--fp-space-5); line-height:1.8;">
      <li><strong>Beginner</strong> — Start with basic greetings and simple verbs</li>
      <li><strong>Elementary</strong> — Start with past tenses and intermediate grammar</li>
      <li><strong>Conversational</strong> — Jump into advanced grammar topics</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section aria-labelledby="faq-heading" style="margin-bottom:var(--fp-space-8);">
    <h2 id="faq-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:var(--fp-space-3);">

      <!--
        Using <details>/<summary> — natively accessible.
        NVDA announces "collapsed" / "expanded".
        Enter or Space toggles. No JavaScript needed.
      -->

      <details class="card" style="cursor:pointer;">
        <summary style="font-weight:600; font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); padding:var(--fp-space-2) 0;">
          How do I navigate the site with a keyboard?
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:var(--fp-space-3) 0 0; line-height:1.6;">
          Use Tab to move forward through the page and Shift+Tab to go back. Press Enter or Space to activate buttons and links. In multiple choice exercises, use the arrow keys to move between options. Every page has a "Skip to main content" link that appears when you press Tab for the first time — use it to jump past the navigation bar.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="card" style="cursor:pointer;">
        <summary style="font-weight:600; font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); padding:var(--fp-space-2) 0;">
          Why does the Check Answer button seem inactive?
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:var(--fp-space-3) 0 0; line-height:1.6;">
          The button stays inactive until you select an answer or type something in the text field. This prevents accidental empty submissions that would count as incorrect. A screen reader will announce the button as "dimmed" until you make a selection, and a text hint below the button tells you what to do.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="card" style="cursor:pointer;">
        <summary style="font-weight:600; font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); padding:var(--fp-space-2) 0;">
          Does capitalization or punctuation matter in translation exercises?
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:var(--fp-space-3) 0 0; line-height:1.6;">
          No. The system ignores uppercase, lowercase, periods, commas, and other punctuation when checking your answer. Only the words matter.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="card" style="cursor:pointer;">
        <summary style="font-weight:600; font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); padding:var(--fp-space-2) 0;">
          How does the word bank exercise work?
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:var(--fp-space-3) 0 0; line-height:1.6;">
          You build a sentence by pressing the word buttons in the correct order. Press Enter or Space to select a word, and it gets added to the sentence above. Use the "Remove last word" button to undo your last selection. When your sentence is complete, press the Check Answer button to submit.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- <details class="card" style="cursor:pointer;">
        <summary style="font-weight:600; font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); padding:var(--fp-space-2) 0;">
          Can I retake the level assessment?
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:var(--fp-space-3) 0 0; line-height:1.6;">
          The assessment can be taken once. If you want to change your level, you can start working on lessons from any level regardless of your assessment result.
        </p>
      </details> -->

      <details class="card" style="cursor:pointer;">
        <summary style="font-weight:600; font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); padding:var(--fp-space-2) 0;">
          What do the XP points mean?
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:var(--fp-text-sm); color:var(--fp-text-2); margin:var(--fp-space-3) 0 0; line-height:1.6;">
          You earn 15 XP for a correct answer and 5 XP just for attempting an exercise. Reading and speaking exercises always award 15 XP since there is no right or wrong answer. Your total XP is shown on the dashboard and progress page.
        </p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Back to dashboard -->
  <div style="margin-top:var(--fp-space-6);">
    <a href="/dashboard" class="btn btn-primary">Back to dashboard</a>
  </div>

</div>
